  "text": "Note that we evaluate κ for different antenna configurations in Sec. IV. Since the maximum cross product of any two steering vectors is M , we see that 0 ≤ κ ≤ 1. Furthermore, if the independent rays in (21) correspond to two different users then κ is seen to be a measure of the normalized interference between the rays. This interpretation is further explored in Sec. VII. Note that κ was also found to be an important performance metric in [CITATION_1] .",
